Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.64,0:00:10.86,TextOver,,0,0,0,,{\fs50\pos(640,672.632)\3c&H743602&\c&HFFFFFF&\1a&H19&}Never give up Baby Special
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.64,0:00:10.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,325.749)}Let's reveal it:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.96,0:00:14.69,BlueFill,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,543.01)\fad(200,0)\c&HE66A4A&}George Tokoro
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.04,0:00:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it "Never give up Baby Special"?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.08,0:00:14.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.88,0:00:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We brought the staff to talk about the special.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.88,0:00:19.83,BlueFill,,0,0,0,,{\move(-12.528,580.044,367.718,576.259,2,300)}My First Errand staff room
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.88,0:00:19.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What is it really like?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.13,0:00:23.17,GreenFill,,0,0,0,,{\pos(488.579,546.278)}Really, when watching from home
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.30,0:00:23.17,BlueFill,,0,0,0,,{\fs65\pos(951.558,509.242)} {\pos(960.272,486.368)}I cry
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.80,0:00:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When I cry in the studio
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.20,0:00:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate being filmed by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.88,0:00:32.78,GreenFill,,0,0,0,,{\fs57.143\pos(663.966,531.029)} I really have to endure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.90,0:00:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's not a cool emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.30,0:00:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the camera is constantly pinned on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.70,0:00:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how much wells up
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.89,0:00:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&HD9875C&\3c&HFFFFFF&\fs50\pos(640,503.798)\4c&H432C73&}I have to suck it back in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.06,0:00:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I try to find ways to dry it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.98,0:00:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I can never express myself fully.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.49,0:00:47.83,RedFill,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,544.099)\4c&H47844B&}I open my eyes fully so
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.83,0:00:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(285.958,493.994)\c&HD2CD6E&}the tears
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.96,0:00:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(535.421,496.173)\c&H30DA5A&}will dry easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.12,0:00:53.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.74,0:00:56.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,How is it for this person?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.54,0:00:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Never give up Baby Special.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.74,0:01:00.24,TextOver,,0,0,0,,{\c&HE61EDB&\pos(640,540.83)\fad(200,200)}Moriguchi Hiroko \N Singer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.14,0:01:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that strike a chord?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.80,0:01:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Never give up baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.26,0:01:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I am sure that this song will play in your heads
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.86,0:01:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as you realize that it's the new theme song.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.92,0:01:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"My first errand".\NI've recorded them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.62,0:01:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And I rewatch them when I need to be moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.38,0:01:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so powerful that I completely cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.42,0:01:23.60,BlueFill,,0,0,0,,{\fs50\pos(285.992,475)\4c&HFF333D&}Complete
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.42,0:01:23.60,GreenFill,,0,0,0,,{\fs50\pos(578.383,475)\4c&H73CCE1&}emotional crying
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.93,0:01:23.60,RedFill,,0,0,0,,{\c&HE70BD9&\fs50\pos(928.069,475)}how refreshing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.16,0:01:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you children.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.84,0:01:27.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Let's cry and feel emotionally refreshed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.16,0:01:29.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,First up
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.16,0:01:33.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The 6 year old bigger brother has a little brother who looks up to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.67,0:01:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(926.187,172.935)\fad(200,200)}Fukuoka ● Kyushu
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.98,0:01:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Kyotaro, dinner is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.08,0:01:40.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The big brother Kyotaro is in \Nthird grade elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.12,0:01:44.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The one going on errand \N is the little brother, Minato.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.76,0:01:46.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He is only 2 years and 8 months old.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.85,0:01:49.15,GreenFill,,0,0,0,,{\pos(909.072,443.752)\fad(200,200)}Minato
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.85,0:01:49.15,GreenFill,,0,0,0,,{\pos(575.08,558.707)\fad(200,200)}2 years \N 8 months old
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.42,0:01:49.89,Studio,,0,0,0,,Will he be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.02,0:01:49.88,Studio,,0,0,0,,I am worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.48,0:01:52.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Big brother, stop playing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.19,0:01:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(865,180)}Kyotaro,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.19,0:01:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(865,410)}dinner is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.80,0:02:00.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Kyotaro, the big brother, went on his first errand when he was 2 years and 3 months old.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.56,0:02:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(951.83,522.381)\fad(200,200)}Kyotaro (big brother)\N Elementary school 3rd grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.42,0:02:01.62,Studio,,0,0,0,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.86,0:02:02.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Well it was for his own ice cream.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.98,0:02:07.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,When his younger brother heard \N he couldn't take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.08,0:02:10.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Isn't it dangerous to go to the apartment complex?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.68,0:02:13.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He wants to assist his brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.41,0:02:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)\pos(606.408,108.931)}I'm leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.16,0:02:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(816.101,364.314)}Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.38,0:02:18.68,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Kyotaro leaves for his penmanship classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.20,0:02:22.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The penmanship school is past the park \N inside the apartment complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.72,0:02:25.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Cars can't go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.12,0:02:27.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Right! Time for Kyotaro's plan
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.16,0:02:29.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,his first errand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.73,0:02:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,200)\pos(980,110)}Minato,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.73,0:02:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,200)\pos(980,258)}Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.67,0:02:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1105.678,173.084)}Your big brother \Nhas forgotten this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.22,0:02:39.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Did he forget it once again? \NIt can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.48,0:02:43.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The goal is to go to the penmanship class \N and give the pen to his big brother Kyotaro.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.51,0:02:46.65,TextOver,,0,0,0,,{\pos(961.265,235.815)}If you go\N\N then say \N\NKyotaro, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.34,0:02:46.75,GreenFill,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.94,0:02:51.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It is one way up the hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.32,0:02:56.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,There are many students in the class \N so he has to call out "Kyotaro brother".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.24,0:03:02.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In order to not scare the 2-year-and-8-month-old boy\N the crew is hiding while filming him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.74,0:03:05.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's raining lightly outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.20,0:03:07.06,Studio,,0,0,0,,Don't slip, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.26,0:03:09.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even when she has to throw out the trash\Nhe hates being apart from his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.22,0:03:11.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What an emotional second son.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.94,0:03:14.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But today there is something that he must do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.76,0:03:18.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Since his forgetful brother is in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.28,0:03:20.74,Studio,,0,0,0,,His shoes are cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.74,0:03:27.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,When being told to wear a raincoat he answers \N"I want to use the umbrella like my big brother"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.34,0:03:30.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He has started to use umbrellas recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.70,0:03:34.22,Studio,,0,0,0,,It must be heavy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.22,0:03:37.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Whoa, all those huge people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.64,0:03:39.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They are middle school students.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.94,0:03:44.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Without mommy \Neverything feels so far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.38,0:03:46.36,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The umbrella feels heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.72,0:03:52.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,1 week from now and \Nhe will be finished with nursery school.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.42,0:03:56.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Growing a little every day \N his mother can't keep up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.84,0:04:00.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,These are the steps leading to the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.12,0:04:05.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Kyotaro brother, \N is doing pretty well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.74,0:04:10.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The entrance to the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.06,0:04:12.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H2CB049&\fad(200,200)\t(\fscx150\fscy150)\pos(640,556.863)}Phew, I arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.18,0:04:17.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Let's show you a brief moment of a growing 2-year-and-8-month-old kid in one cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.42,0:04:19.12,Studio,,0,0,0,,He is putting it in like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.10,0:04:23.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,No, the umbrella can't go in like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.40,0:04:28.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"Oh, so it can't go in like that."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.26,0:04:32.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,No no no, this isn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.58,0:04:36.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Oh? Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.56,0:04:38.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, yes. That's how you close it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.16,0:04:42.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Exactly. That's how.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.86,0:04:42.54,Studio,,0,0,0,,He did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.26,0:04:45.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Doing like others. Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.68,0:04:50.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Oh no, it can't stay still.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.90,0:04:52.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He thought of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.06,0:05:01.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Finally managed to put the umbrella in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.85,0:05:03.92,GreenFill,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H2CB049&\fad(200,200)\t(\fscx150\fscy150)\pos(640,563.263)}Pheew
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.50,0:05:06.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,From here he will call his brother. \N Do it in a loud voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.10,0:05:10.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H2CB049&\clip(566,512,598,566)\t(0,600,\clip(550,512,741,570))\pos(640,555)}Kyotaro
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.76,0:05:14.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H2CB049&\clip(330,495,381,581)\pos(640,555)\t(0,1800,\clip(345,512,966,573))\fad(0,200)}Kyotaro, your dinner is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.40,0:05:18.60,Studio,,0,0,0,,Dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.94,0:05:23.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Though a bit embarrassing for his big brother \N he couldn't help himself from being so worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.24,0:05:26.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Minato, \N You sure have a great big brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.68,0:05:29.00,Studio,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.82,0:05:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you Minato.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.78,0:05:36.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Brother, if you forget it again \NI will bring it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.72,0:05:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,200)\pos(863.32,193.139)}After these stairs \N will you go \N by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.22,0:05:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you go back alone? \NMom is waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.88,0:05:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.52,0:05:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Splish splosh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:52.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Big brobro, make sure to do it well. \N He parts with that emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.24,0:06:01.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Hold on. My head feels wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.02,0:06:03.94,Studio,,0,0,0,,Umbrella, umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.94,0:06:04.82,Studio,,0,0,0,,The umbrella!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.82,0:06:07.56,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He has forgotten what it is that he has forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.68,0:06:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&H2CB049&\clip(406,514,448,570)\pos(640,555)\t(0,1000,\clip(398,520,899,575))}Mommy, open up, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.68,0:06:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you come running?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.76,0:06:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(892,189)}You are \Nawesome,\N Minato.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.19,0:06:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,200)\pos(876,154)}Where is \N the umbrella?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.40,0:06:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you forget the umbrella there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.14,0:06:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, even though you went all the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.53,0:06:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1056.937,189.587)}You forgot \N the umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.54,0:06:34.21,TextOver,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,200)\pos(901.634,161.063)}Just like your\N big brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.60,0:06:37.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yes, just like his brother. \N He forgot it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.46,0:06:44.82,BlueFill,,0,0,0,,{\move(-12.528,580.044,350.288,587.15,2,300)}My First Errand staff room
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.46,0:06:45.16,Studio,,0,0,0,,{\pos(241.293,195.537)}So this is how \N the cameramen \Ndisguise themselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.00,0:06:45.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In the staff room we keep the disguises.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.96,0:06:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This looks good on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.92,0:06:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute. This isn't the reason why I am here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.32,0:06:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You have collected the request letters here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.28,0:06:59.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The mothers send us letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.08,0:07:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody, they really have gathered all the letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.40,0:07:06.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,For the mothers, the memories of the first errand
